  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-06-14",
    "date": "2007-07-18T19:39:59Z",
    "text": "Small Business SOX Compliance Extension Act - Directs the Securities and Exchange Commission to modify its regulations under the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002 (SOX) for annual management assessments of, and reports on, internal financial controls.\n\nRequires such regulations to provide that a non-accelerated filer does not have to provide management's report on internal control over financial reporting until it files an annual report for its first fiscal year ending on or after December 15, 2008 (thereby extending the current moratorium on such requirements for small businesses)."
  },
